      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay but if the research is so \"mixed,\" it feels like people just say it's negligible to avoid the controversy. if you look at the actual math, isn't it basically a fact that increasing the supply of labor naturally drives prices—in this case, wages—down? it seems like a basic supply and demand rule that eludes the most objective economists.",
